2
00:01:50,050 --> 00:02:00,040
Your media player does not support the subtitle format used in this episode.
Subtitles will likely not function properly.
Please use one of the recommended video players, preferably mpv:
https://mpv.io

3
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:56,350
What? They rushed off the island?

4
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:59,470
Yes. We couldn't even
give them our gift.

5
00:01:59,470 --> 00:02:01,810
What a pity...

6
00:02:02,980 --> 00:02:07,650
I wonder if they even realize
how grateful we are for what they did.

7
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:13,110
Indeed. They still don't
grasp our feelings.

8
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:18,410
It's not fair, Aisa...

9
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:20,830
You're the only one who got
to say goodbye to them.

10
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:24,670
They can't stop talking about
how we let our saviors run away.

11
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:29,670
But Luffy and the others
told me not to tell anyone.

12
00:02:30,340 --> 00:02:34,630
Hey Raki, did you know that
Luffy's body stretches?!

13
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:37,800
He'd be like, "Gum-Gum Pistol!"

14
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,430
Hey, Aisa, hold still!

15
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:43,390
Who knew there was a strong
warrior in the Blue Sea, too?!

16
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:48,060
I wanna be like him,
like "Gum-Gum...!"

17
00:02:49,610 --> 00:02:51,070
Aisa...

18
00:02:52,570 --> 00:02:56,030
Let's just give it a trim for today.
You should let your hair grow out.

19
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:56,860
What?

20
00:02:56,860 --> 00:03:01,540
I'm sure it'll look good on you.
You're a girl, so you should look cute.

21
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:06,170
Cute?! Me?!

22
00:03:07,670 --> 00:03:08,420
That's right!

23
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:12,670
Now that there's no need
for you kids to carry weapons...

24
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:19,100
you can live freely,
like people in the sky should.

25
00:03:21,140 --> 00:03:23,350
You sure are ladylike today!

26
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:27,270
Now, hold still, Aisa!

27
00:03:27,270 --> 00:03:28,650
Ladylike Raki!

28
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:29,900
Aisa!

29
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,990
Great Warrior Kalgara...

30
00:03:39,870 --> 00:03:43,490
We were told that the sacred duty
of the Shandians had been fulfilled.

31
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:47,710
And I'm sure your best friend
heard your wish as well.

32
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:53,340
Future generations will no longer
need to shed their blood.

33
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:59,010
Our fight may be over...
but we will never lose our pride!

34
00:03:59,590 --> 00:04:03,100
So please continue to watch over us.

35
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:09,310
We swear to always keep
the Light of Shandora shining!

36
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:23,030
I am merely the Sky Knight,
a freelance mercenary.

37
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,370
You are far better suited for it.

38
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:29,670
This city belonged to your
people from the start.

39
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:31,210
What's this now?

40
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:34,130
That's not a good reason.

41
00:04:34,130 --> 00:04:36,960
I think this battle
taught us all the hard truth...

42
00:04:37,590 --> 00:04:40,640
that no one can claim
ownership of vearth.

43
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:43,390
The title of "god" provides strength.

44
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:47,100
The name of the land is Skypiea.
The name of the city is Shandora.

45
00:04:47,930 --> 00:04:50,020
The only person who
can unify them is you,

46
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:55,610
the one who's always anguished over
this land's never-ending war.

47
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:59,490
Sky Knight Gan Fall...

48
00:04:59,490 --> 00:05:01,570
I ask you to take the seat of god once more

49
00:05:01,570 --> 00:05:05,490
and give this ailing nation
the strength to heal.

50
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,410
We'd like you to, as well!

51
00:05:09,410 --> 00:05:10,500
Lord Gan Fall!

52
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:12,630
As long as it's you,
we're on board too!

53
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:13,710
Yeah!

54
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:15,040
Gan Fall!

55
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,210
God!

56
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:16,920
We need you!

57
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,430
Alas...

58
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:28,890
Just when I thought I could finally
grow pumpkins in peace...

59
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:57,210
Everyone! We can see it now!

60
00:05:58,380 --> 00:06:01,420
Take a look ahead! It's Cloud End!

61
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:02,630
Ah! Lemme see!

62
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:06,930
Wow... So we can go
back down over there?

63
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:09,100
We got here sooner than I thought.

64
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:13,980
Do we have to leave already?

65
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:17,690
Yeah, now that we're heading back,
I don't want to say goodbye.

66
00:06:17,690 --> 00:06:20,570
It's time to say farewell
to this pure white sea.

67
00:06:20,570 --> 00:06:23,740
The sky island was fun...
but it was scary, too.

68
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:28,700
So there's a milky road through there that
heads straight down to the Blue Sea, huh?

69
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:32,120
I wonder if we'll ever visit
the sky island again...

70
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:33,960
Maybe, maybe not.

71
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:47,260
Well then, everyone! I'm sorry,
but we'll say goodbye here!

72
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:49,060
Please take care, everyone!

73
00:06:49,890 --> 00:06:51,720
Thanks for seeing us off!

74
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,390
Conis! Take care of yourself!

75
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:56,350
Send our regards to the others, too!

76
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:58,900
See you!

77
00:06:59,650 --> 00:07:01,690
Thanks for everything!

78
00:07:02,690 --> 00:07:07,160
No! We should be thanking you!

79
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:10,990
I'll never forget you all!

80
00:07:11,490 --> 00:07:14,330
Conis, old guy, and fluff ball!
You all take care!

81
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,500
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

82
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:19,540
Now, furl the sails immediately
and hold on tight to the ship!

83
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,670
Alright! Let's do as he says!

84
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:23,970
Sounds like it's gonna go pretty fast!

85
00:07:23,970 --> 00:07:27,760
Yeah, we're sliding 7,000
meters down! Hurry!

86
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,760
– Okay!
– Okay!

87
00:07:33,930 --> 00:07:35,020
Wh-What?! Huh?!

88
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:40,060
He says, "Don't forget about me."

89
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:43,860
Oh... It's that south bird we
brought to the sky with us.

90
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,530
Okay, Captain!

91
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:51,160
We got the log for the next island!

92
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:59,880
Alright! Once we get back down,
we'll start a brand new adventure!

93
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:03,090
You ready, guys?!

94
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:07,340
We're going back to the Blue Sea!

95
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:08,760
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

96
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:25,400
Everyone! Be careful while dropping!

97
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,610
– Dropping?
– Dropping?

98
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:41,000
Heso!

99
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:50,050
Here we go! The sky island's
famous octoballoon!

100
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:04,400
An octopus!

101
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,280
You son of a...!

102
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:11,450
O-Ouch...

103
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:14,410
Wh-Wh-What the...?!

104
00:09:16,370 --> 00:09:18,910
Hey, look! This is so cool!

105
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:22,750
What the hell is this?!

106
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:24,090
It's a balloon!

107
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,630
This is fun!

108
00:09:26,630 --> 00:09:27,710
We've slowed down!

109
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:32,970
I... I thought that I was finally
gonna go to the netherworld.

110
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:06,170
Ring it! Let the ringing of the bell bid
farewell to the saviors of this land!

111
00:10:06,170 --> 00:10:07,090
Heso!

112
00:10:09,590 --> 00:10:13,090
Luffy! Let's meet again!

113
00:10:13,090 --> 00:10:14,800
Don't be a stranger!

114
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,600
Thank you!

115
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:20,430
Safe travels back to the Blue Sea!

116
00:10:27,110 --> 00:10:29,610
When you cast your gaze
toward the sky...

117
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:34,660
Is it real, or is it but a dream,
this God Land above the clouds?

118
00:10:35,450 --> 00:10:37,450
Ten thousand meters high in the sky...

119
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:41,040
If you listen closely, you can
hear the sound of a bell.

120
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:43,960
It rings today. And it will
ring again tomorrow.

121
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:47,290
The echoing sound
of the bell in the sky

122
00:10:47,290 --> 00:10:51,760
sings of the triumph of this
wandering land...

123
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,430
This is cool!

124
00:11:02,430 --> 00:11:06,940
Yeah! This is great!

125
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:10,980
You're calling off the search?!

126
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:14,990
It's only natural, right?!
The City of Gold was in the sky.

127
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:18,160
We won't find anything
at the bottom of the sea.

128
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:20,160
This is the end.

129
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:22,490
There's no point in staying here.

130
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,080
Boss...

131
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,170
Boss...

132
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:33,840
I sincerely thank you all... for joining me
in pursuit of my dream all these years.

133
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,300
What are you saying...?

134
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,640
Don't treat us like strangers...

135
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:38,970
Well then, gentlemen!

136
00:11:41,890 --> 00:11:44,850
What sort of romantic adventure
shall we go after next?!

137
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:54,360
We'll follow you to the ends
of the world, boss!

138
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:03,290
Gold! Gold! Gold! Gold! Gold!

139
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:07,920
We're finally super rich!
What're we gonna buy?!

140
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:11,250
What about a huge bronze statue?!

141
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:14,590
You moron! Why would you
trade gold for bronze?!

142
00:12:14,590 --> 00:12:16,840
We should stock up on cannons!

143
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,180
Let's buy ten of them! Ten!

144
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:21,550
Nami! I want
a refrigerator with a lock!

145
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:25,890
Don't be stupid! What're we gonna
do when we get hungry?! I object!

146
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:25,470
I... I... I want you to
buy me some books!

147
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:27,980
That's why we should
buy it, dumbass!

148
00:12:25,470 --> 00:12:27,980
I wanna read medical
books from other countries!

149
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:30,060
Now hold on just a second, you guys!

150
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:34,230
We'll split the treasure once
we get back down, okay?

151
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:35,900
Please buy books for me!

152
00:12:36,570 --> 00:12:40,410
If we spend our money willy-nilly,
we'll end up wasting it all.

153
00:12:40,410 --> 00:12:41,740
Miss Navigator...

154
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:45,580
Where exactly is this ship headed?

155
00:12:45,580 --> 00:12:47,040
Where?

156
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,410
The next island...

157
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:53,250
What?! What?!

158
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:54,300
What's wrong?

159
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:57,010
What's wrong, Nami?

160
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,630
Crap!

161
00:13:00,630 --> 00:13:03,760
We must've hit an air current,
and now we're drifting!

162
00:13:04,890 --> 00:13:05,930
An air current?!

163
00:13:05,930 --> 00:13:08,180
Come to think of it,
there is a breeze...

164
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:09,560
Is that bad?

165
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:10,940
Of course it is!

166
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:13,520
We can't predict where we'll land now!

167
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:15,360
What are we gonna do?

168
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:19,360
We can't set the sails
and control the ship like this.

169
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:21,360
Hey, don't worry.

170
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:24,030
We'll get to the next island eventually.

171
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:27,700
You say it like it's
no big deal, as usual...

172
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:28,660
Hold on...

173
00:13:29,660 --> 00:13:31,710
What is it, Sanji?

174
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:34,170
Well... maybe it's my imagination...

175
00:13:34,170 --> 00:13:35,170
Huh?

176
00:13:35,170 --> 00:13:36,300
What is?

177
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,670
No. Never mind...

178
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:40,340
There's a problem! Hey!

179
00:13:45,350 --> 00:13:46,890
Oh, it was just a dream.

180
00:13:46,890 --> 00:13:48,220
Do you want me to freak out?!

181
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:51,140
Dammit, Moss Head!
I'm gonna fillet your ass!

182
00:13:49,220 --> 00:13:51,140
You scared me!

183
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:54,810
Now, now, Zoro's just tired
after our battle in the clouds...

184
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:05,620
The sun's completely set now.

185
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:07,200
It's a nice view, though.

186
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,910
Yeah, you're right.

187
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,040
What's all the ruckus?!

188
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,420
Run!

189
00:14:18,050 --> 00:14:20,760
Quit pushing! W-We gotta
stay away from 'em!

190
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:21,720
A falling out?!

191
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,020
Bellamy!

192
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:37,400
Sarquiss!

193
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,150
Please! Make him stop!

194
00:14:39,860 --> 00:14:44,950
Please! Just stop it!
Why are you doing this...?!

195
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,870
What's happening?!

196
00:14:46,870 --> 00:14:49,030
Sarquiss is the one begging to stop?

197
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:52,750
Why? Why, you ask?

198
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:55,830
Sarquiss... Bellamy...

199
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:01,460
It's because you disrespected
my flag, of course.

200
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:07,430
"Does the sky island exist or not?"

201
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:11,270
"Is the City of Gold real or not?"

202
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:16,150
I couldn't care less about any of that.

203
00:15:16,810 --> 00:15:20,110
"Pit belief against belief
to gain control over others."

204
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:22,530
That's what I told you...

205
00:15:22,530 --> 00:15:24,570
wasn't it, Bellamy?

206
00:15:25,860 --> 00:15:29,120
That's... Donquixote Doflamingo!

207
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,790
He's one of the Seven
Warlords of the Sea!

208
00:15:31,790 --> 00:15:34,410
His bounty used to be
over 300 million!

209
00:15:34,410 --> 00:15:36,460
What's a guy like him doing here?!

210
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:41,590
I don't need useless punks
like you serving under me...

211
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:44,760
Crap! My body's moving on its own!

212
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:47,800
Stop! Please, don't...!

213
00:15:48,220 --> 00:15:50,640
No!

214
00:15:54,310 --> 00:15:55,310
Bellamy!

215
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:01,820
G-Give me...

216
00:16:02,570 --> 00:16:05,690
Give me one more chance...!

217
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:10,320
I'll... We'll be your loyal followers!

218
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,530
Bellamy!

219
00:16:11,530 --> 00:16:13,160
No more, Bellamy!

220
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:19,290
Yes, I lost, but I never went
against your principles!

221
00:16:19,290 --> 00:16:20,920
I swear on your flag!

222
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:23,590
This is just my way of doing things!

223
00:16:23,590 --> 00:16:26,130
We couldn't just run him off!

224
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:29,300
He would've reached you someday!

225
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:33,850
How very touching,
O faithful subordinate of mine.

226
00:16:34,180 --> 00:16:38,730
That's what I like about you, Bellamy.

227
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:45,650
A new era is just around
the corner. Do as you wish.

228
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:50,240
However... I don't need you anymore.

229
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:56,040
Doflamingo!

230
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:05,250
He just took out a notorious rookie
worth 55 million!

231
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:07,010
It was child's play to him!

232
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:10,590
It's finally beginning!

233
00:17:10,590 --> 00:17:13,010
You'd better be prepared!

234
00:17:13,010 --> 00:17:16,890
A world where only true pirates
can survive is drawing near!

235
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:19,270
The powerless among you—
run while you can!

236
00:17:19,270 --> 00:17:21,270
With the inevitable tides of time,

237
00:17:21,270 --> 00:17:24,770
a new era of champions
will soon be upon us!

238
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:31,570
It's taking quite a long time
to reach the Blue Sea.

239
00:17:31,570 --> 00:17:36,200
I'm worried how far
the ship will drift off course.

240
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:39,710
Oh?! Then shall I sing a love song
to take your mind off it?

241
00:17:39,710 --> 00:17:40,870
Shut up!

242
00:17:43,170 --> 00:17:46,550
It'd be pretty convenient
if we drifted to Laugh Tale, huh?

243
00:17:46,550 --> 00:17:48,380
Usopp! That'd be so cool!

244
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:50,010
That's not possible.

245
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:51,840
To get to Laugh Tale,

246
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:55,140
we still have to traverse
over half the Grand Line.

247
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:58,350
Uh, well, yeah... I knew that.

248
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:01,770
Alright, I'm officially bored.

249
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:04,480
When are we gonna reach the sea?

250
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:05,810
Oh, just go back to sleep.

251
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:09,070
If you're bored, come here, Zoro!

252
00:18:09,070 --> 00:18:11,280
This is fun!

253
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:13,200
Oh? Luffy?

254
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,740
Where's his voice coming from?

255
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:17,740
It sounded pretty far away.

256
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,870
Luffy! Where are you?!

257
00:18:19,870 --> 00:18:21,750
I'm up here!

258
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:23,920
Everyone, come check this out!

259
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:25,790
This is so much fun!

260
00:18:26,340 --> 00:18:28,000
Ugh! So he is up there!

261
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:33,720
Awesome! This is the best!

262
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:38,640
Hey! Be careful, Luffy!

263
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:41,640
Our lives depend on that balloon!

264
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,600
It's fine! It's fine!

265
00:18:50,030 --> 00:18:51,900
Knock it off, Luffy!
Get down here now!

266
00:18:52,530 --> 00:18:53,950
Hey, Luffy, stop it!

267
00:18:53,950 --> 00:18:56,070
What's the matter now, Sanji?

268
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:57,870
The octopus is shrinking!

269
00:18:57,870 --> 00:19:00,040
If he keeps doing that, we'll fall!

270
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:00,580
What?!

271
00:19:00,580 --> 00:19:02,790
Hey, Luffy!

272
00:19:02,790 --> 00:19:04,290
What's going on?

273
00:19:04,290 --> 00:19:06,170
He said the octopus is shrinking!

274
00:19:06,170 --> 00:19:06,880
What?!

275
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:10,340
Now that you mention it,
it does look smaller than before.

276
00:19:10,340 --> 00:19:13,340
What are we gonna do?!
We're still pretty high up!

277
00:19:13,340 --> 00:19:15,550
I wonder if it'll last
until we reach the sea...

278
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:20,470
Hey, Luffy! Come back down!
Something's wrong!

279
00:19:34,990 --> 00:19:38,570
That was scary! It stopped
bouncing out of nowhere!

280
00:19:38,570 --> 00:19:41,280
I was trying to tell you
the octopus is shrinking!

281
00:19:47,620 --> 00:19:50,880
H-Huh? I didn't move,
but we're back to the ship!

282
00:19:51,550 --> 00:19:53,760
We're falling! We're falling!

283
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:56,590
This is bad!

284
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:58,430
At this speed, we'll sink instantly!

285
00:19:58,430 --> 00:20:00,300
We might not even hit water!

286
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:02,140
Ugh! That's right! Dammit!

287
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:04,350
What are you doing, Usopp?!

288
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:05,520
What else?!

289
00:20:05,930 --> 00:20:07,520
Protecting the ship!

290
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,860
What're you gonna do?!

291
00:20:12,860 --> 00:20:14,530
Be careful, Usopp!

292
00:20:16,150 --> 00:20:19,570
Usopp Aah-eeh-aaaaaah!

293
00:20:25,910 --> 00:20:29,040
Phew, success! Alright...

294
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:33,550
I'm gonna use all
the breath dials I have...

295
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:36,800
There!

296
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,760
Float!

297
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:47,350
We slowed down.

298
00:20:47,350 --> 00:20:48,440
Nice!

299
00:20:48,810 --> 00:20:50,190
So we're safe?

300
00:20:50,190 --> 00:20:51,860
Looks like it.

301
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:55,480
Did you see the amazing job I did?!

302
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:57,240
Usopp, you're so cool!

303
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:01,240
For a moment, I wasn't
sure if we'd make it!

304
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,490
Yeah, seriously...

305
00:21:02,490 --> 00:21:04,330
I thought that was it.

306
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,040
Why?!

307
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:12,250
Usopp!

308
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:19,550
Everyone! Grab something
and hold on tight!

309
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:33,360
It's freezing...!

310
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:36,190
Nami! Robin! Are you okay?

311
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:41,700
That startled me! The octopus
suddenly shrank all the way!

312
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,370
Maybe it was an air leak.

313
00:21:43,370 --> 00:21:45,030
What the heck happened?!

314
00:21:47,790 --> 00:21:50,870
Well, we somehow made
it down... without dying.

315
00:21:50,870 --> 00:21:52,580
Thanks a bunch!

316
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,380
Still...

317
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:01,930
we really went to an
incredible place, didn't we?

318
00:22:01,930 --> 00:22:04,970
Now that we're down here,
it seems so far away.

319
00:22:04,970 --> 00:22:07,010
It's like we were dreaming.

320
00:22:07,390 --> 00:22:10,520
It's a dream land. I wonder
if we can go visit again some day.

321
00:22:10,850 --> 00:22:13,230
You might be able to
get closer if you die.

322
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:16,400
Zoro, do you really think
you'll be allowed into heaven?

323
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:18,150
Shut it!

324
00:22:18,150 --> 00:22:20,820
At any rate, things have calmed down.

325
00:22:20,820 --> 00:22:22,400
I'll make coffee or something.

326
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,530
Better yet, make us
some dinner, Sanji!

327
00:22:24,530 --> 00:22:28,030
Yeah, yeah, I'll get right on it.
Just sit tight and have some coffee.

328
00:22:28,030 --> 00:22:29,740
Okay...

329
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:32,080
By the way...

330
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:51,220
Where the heck...

331
00:22:51,730 --> 00:22:54,100
are we?!

332
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:50,910
Lower Skypiea,
the White Sea

333
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:50,910
Lower Skypiea,
the White Sea

334
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:50,910
Lower Skypiea,
the White Sea
